text: A general election was held on 9 April 1992 to elect all 651 members to the House of Commons of the United Kingdom. The Conservative Party won the election, winning 336 seats, and John Major stayed as Prime Minister. Many people thought that the Labour Party would win the election because opinion polls had shown them to be ahead. ==Notes== ==References== Category:1992 elections Category:United Kingdom general elections
title: 1992 United Kingdom general election
